collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Celebration Overture, based on 10,000 Men of Harvard, was Gordon Jacob's last completed work. Duration: ca. 8 minutes.
Scored for wind ensemble: 3 flutes, 2 oboes, 2 clarinets, 4 horns, 3 trumpets, 3 trombones, tuba, timpani, and percussion.

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: As the title implies, the work expresses the deep religious emotions of the promises made by God to mankind. Two thematic elements are employed: the first, a dramatic proclamation, is introduced by horns and subsequently taken bytrumpets and woodwinds - the second plaintive theme, in the manner of a supplication, is presented by oboes followed by flutes and clarinets. The first theme returns leading to a climactic

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: As implied by the title, Credo is in the nature of a profession of faith. Organized in a tripartite form, the opening section presents a four-note motif contrasted with a chorale-like melody in the woodwinds. The slower middlesection is more contrite and reflective, the polyphonic texture in the woodwinds being imitated by a similar setting in the brasses. The final section employs development of the material from

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Symphonic Band (score & parts). Tull, F

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Symphonic Band (score & parts). Piston, W

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Symphonic Band (score & parts). Nixon, R

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Duration: ca. 2 1/2 minutes

The Mad Major was Alford's first post-war march, written and published in 1921. Like Colonel Bogey, with which the series began, it is cast in a double three-part form, the first of which allows the tune of the A part to serve,conveniently, as counterpoint to B.
Colonel Bogey was composed in 1913 at Fort George and published just in time to be around when the world unfortunately found itself in a very big war. Duration: 3 1/2 minutes.
A Symphonic Band arrangement of the famous  Radetsky March  by Johann Strauss I. Available here are the score and parts.

A delightful theme and variations for young and beginner ensembles. This thoughtful and satisfying arrangement assigns varying skill sets to bring out different colours of a simple theme. Optional percussion elements add interest and texture.

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Symphonic Band (score & parts). Vaughan, William

collection: Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
Boosey and Hawkes Quarter Military Band
description: Written for the Blue Lake Fine Arts Camp.

sous_titre: a sparkling review marches and counter marches

description: This medley features three seldom heard sea songs: Johnny Come Down to Hilo, The Sailor's Alphabet and Sailing at High Tide. It is orchestrated to showcase the various color combinations within the beginning band.
Junior Wind Band (score & parts). Wastall, P
Junior Wind Band (score & parts). Wastall, P

titre: On the Quarterdeck (Wind Band March Card Set )

description: Dating from World War I while Sousa was serving in the Naval Reserve, "Bullets and Bayonets" is one of Sousa's most stirring military and patriotic marches. This brilliant "Sousa Legacy" edition incorporates Sousa performance practices and style, as meticulously researched by Sousa scholar Keith Brion. An excellent choice for better school bands as well as adult community bands, "Bullets and Bayonets" will thrill

"The Pathfinder Of Panama" was composed in 1915 for San Francisco’s Panama Pacific Exhibition, a world’s fair honoring the historic completion of the Panama Canal. Filled with energy, this great march captures the moment of national excitement when the opening of the Canal shortened the shipping route between America’s coasts by 13,000 miles. This modern edition presents this fabulous march in a format accessible to

One of the most elegant marches ever written, this 1904 Sousa classic march is often compared to an elegantly dressed diplomat strolling happily down the street while tipping his top hat to the passersby. The music is likewise perfectly dressed, sunny and well appointed. A march of beauty and grace rather than bombast. Excellent music for any performance situation!

This sparkling setting, still as fresh as any recent Broadway medley and never before available, includes the show’s best-loved ballads, rollicking patter songs and the rousing finale. The music has been a continuous hit from its 1879 opening through today. Sousa’s brilliant 1880 orchestration perfectly captures the happy-go-lucky spirit of Sullivan’s show. In this first published edition, Sousa’s superb and

Sousa’s brilliant, fiery and tuneful 3/4 Spanish dance “The Flashing Eyes of Andalusia,” is enhanced by multiple percussion including colorful castanets and tambourines. Sousa’s natural affinity for creating great melodies and his love for the music of the Iberian Peninsula are beautifully joined together. Ideal for concert or contest, and now available for the first time in print.

At the end of WW I Sousa seized on a happy moment of victory to compose a joyous song of celebration welcoming home the returning troops. His stirring “march song” is now available in a new edition for concert band. It can be also used with band and optional voice(s). Vocal text by Sousa’s daughter Helen is included.
titre: When The Boys Come Sailing Home

description: Sousa’s unique and never-before published concert “grand march” was composed as a tribute to two other popular American composers, Stephen Foster and Ethelbert Nevin. Along with an original Sousa march theme it includes Foster’s “Come Where My Love Lies Dreaming” and Nevin’s still widely familiar tune “Narcissus.” All three of the melodies: Sousa, Foster and Nevin, combine in multi-layered splendor for the riotous

A “barn-burner” from the Big Apple. Sousa’s hustle-bustle “New York march” captures both the brilliant, restless energy and the soaring lyrical themes inspired by mid-town Manhattan in 1915. Arranged with all of the style, excitement, and vividly colorful details of the Sousa Band’s own performances. Sousa’s Band played frequently in New York’s enormous “Hippodrome Theater,” a predecessor of today’s Radio City Music

“Sound Off” has what everyone is looking for in an original Sousa march: accessible keys, moderate march tempo, duple meter and reasonable ranges. Wonderful melodies, strong low brass writing. Powerfully depicts the splendor and pomp of the Marine Band on parade at the White House. Authentic Sousa-styled edition.

"Sing it with a spirit that will start the world along". This truly masterful patrol arrangement happily captures all of the joy of the words and music of a great 1865 post-Civil War tune. Sousa’s spirited instrumental setting of Henry Clay Work’s exuberant song is a perfect concert selection.

This is the first concert-sized publication of the superb Sousa-Damrosch "Star Spangled Banner." Their Ab version remains one of the most standard and sing-able arrangements of our National Anthem. It was richly harmonized in 1917 by Walter Damrosch and skillfully arranged by John Philip Sousa. This arrangement has been carefully editied by Keith Brion. The full score includes fascinating historical background.

An absolutely stunning composition created by combining sections from several of Sousa’s arrangements of “Yankee Doodle”. The main section, the “fugue” is taken from Sousa’s “International Congress” and while every note of these arrangements was written by Sousa, Keith Brion and Loras Schissel have combined them into one piece that is certain to become one of his big hits! PERFECT!
This special edition has been created from the original Sousa traveling band’s parts and includes extensive rehearsal and program notes for directors about the performance practices of the period.

NEVER BEFORE PUBLISHED. Written shortly before his death, Sousa’s “The Untitled March” was never performed during his lifetime because a page of the original was misplaced until it was located by Sousa researcher Loras Schissel in 1989. Keith Brion & Loras Schissel have restored the missing music and then edited the march to conform to the standard performance practices of that time using Sousa’s original copy.

Light and whimsical with a slight rag-time flavor, Sousa wrote this as a tribute to the management and patrons of Philadelphia’s Willow Grove Park where his band played hundreds of concerts. Perfect as encore piece!

NEVER BEFORE PUBLISHED, Sousa’s wonderful concert medley of well-known hymns, exactly as performed by the Sousa Band to open all of their Sunday Concerts. Includes: Verdi Requiem, Rock of Ages, Steal Away, Mary & Martha, The Palms, and Nearer My God To Thee (exactly as performed at President Garfield’s funeral).
titre: Songs of Grace and Songs of Glory

description: An exuberant and very impressive contest piece that's very playable! Written in the festive overture style, it features bold melodic and percussive sections which contrast dramatically with lyrical woodwind passages.
This bold and brilliant work effectively portrays the spirit and pageantry of a regal coronation ceremony in three contrasting and colorful movements.

This original work will add depth to any of your concert or contest programs! Although its character is on the lighter side, the textures range from rather innocent to something just this side of sinister. High in musical appeal, this lively and interesting composition is impressive from the fanfare like introduction to its powerful conclusion.
Here's the familiar march theme from the hit TV series of the same name! This sparkling arrangement is perfect for bands of many levels.
Reminiscent of Jay's superb "Parade of the Tall Ships" but at an easier level, this dynamic overture is certain to become a standard. An outstanding opener for your next concert!

The tonal resources of the modern concert band lend themselves perfectly to Bach's classic and powerful work. The highly recommended adaptation by Steve Anthenien makes a truly rewarding musical experience.

An incredible concert work by noted composer Jay Chattaway that you’ll have to experience for yourself. This popular contemporary tone poem successfully evokes the moods and spirit of an American Indian saga. A outstanding concert or contest selection that your students and audiences will love!
Catchy calypso rhythms highlight this delightful treatment that features the "Banana Boat Song" and "Jamaican Farewell," both arranged with a wonderful variety of instrumental colors.
In this case, the "Woods" is not a reference to a forest, but your clarinet section! Both your players and the audience will enjoy this delightful and tuneful number.
Another highly impressive overture for young bands by Elliot Del Borgo. A slow, rich opening is perfectly contrasted by a driving, rhythmic section. Highly recommended for contest or concert!

Here's an overture that your young players will thoroughly enjoy! A tuneful, lyrical middle section contrasts with the rhythmic opening and powerful concluding statements. Perfect for concert or festival use.
Dedicated to the valiant men and women of our military, this solidly scored march has an intriguing modal flavor and is ideally suited for young bands. They'll play it with pride!
Feature your choice of soloist (Flute, Clarinet, Trumpet or Alto Sax) in this enchanting ballad with a light rock touch.
Young piano students will recognize this tuneful and enjoyable little Schumann march. Jerry Nowak has adapted it perfectly for developing bands.
Feature your entire percussion section on this highly entertaining number that's expertly scored for younger players.
This driving rock number by Jerry Nowak will quickly be an audience favorite. It's also the kind of piece guaranteed to keep your players' enthusiasm up!
Here's the theme from the ever-popular TV show in an arrangement by Les Taylor that's perfectly suited for the First Concert Series. "Jeopardy!" can't miss being a real audience favorite!
Here's an inventive new treatment of the well-known calypso favorite. Bill Holcombe's outstanding arrangement is especially effective with quite inexperienced groups.

This blues number lets you spotlight the entire flute section. In addition to making a delightful program addition, "Flute Street" will be an entertaining and effective way to introduce the jazz/blues style to young players.
Here's Australia's well-known melody arranged in march style by a fine Australian composer.
"Chaparral" is an exciting and melodic adventure into the "Old West." With its expansive themes and dramatic nature, your band will really enjoy this spectacular concert or contest composition!
This tuneful march is sure to have your young players sounding their best with minimal rehearsal time. A sure-fire hit for young bands!
Just what the doctor ordered! Here's a really fun and easy to-play piece skillfully written for young bands. But be careful, they may not want to play anything else!
This highly playable arrangement of Offenbach's lively Can Can is instantly recognizable by all. This fine version is just right for young players.

This outstanding arrangement introduces your young musicians to some classic music! Features themes from "Academic Festival Overture" and the "First Symphony." A useful and important addition to your band library!
Here's a bold and exciting composition that's perfect for young players. The exciting Spanish style will have even very inexperienced bands sounding their best in no time.
Here's a great arrangement of the theme from the top-rated TV show. Spotlighting your percussion section, it's guaranteed to be a favorite with your band and audiences!

Featuring the entire clarinet section, this delightful piece is easy to play and certain to be a highlight on any program. There is also an opportunity to feature your best clarinet player with a solo cadenza. Enchanting!
Here's an exciting "Western"-styled composition that features a powerful main theme and a contrasting lyrical middle section. Very effective!
That's right! A polka for very young band. Just wait until you see the response it generates on your next concert.
Focusing on lyrical and expressive elements, Jerry Nowak's meaningful composition makes for a very impressive concert or contest selection.

After a dramatic fanfare-like opening, the spirited main theme is presented, propelled along by a driving snare drum part. Strong themes and powerful rhythms make this exciting composition a fine choice for any contest or concert program

There are interesting parts for all players in this easy and tuneful selection. The calypso beat helps keep things flowing along naturally and your young group will be sounding their best in no time at all!

Dedicated to the Statue of Liberty, SYMBOL OF FREEDOM opens with a tuneful main theme which may be whistled by the band. This very playable, dramatic sounding and powerful march is one of Jay Chattaway's finest!
Your young flute section will really love this enchanting feature. SERENATA is comprised of two sections, each of which may be programmed separately. You definitely won't want to miss this one!
A medley of two spirituals, the beautiful "Sometimes I Feel Like A Motherless Child" and a lively rock-styled treatment of "Everytime I Feel The Spirit." A real crowd pleaser!
Strong melodic themes and colorful percussion are featured in this dramatic selection that successfully captures the flavor and moods of Spain. It's sure to add lots of excitement to any program!
Characterized by refreshing melodic lines and harmonies, this appealing lyrical trumpet feature can be performed as a solo, duet or with the entire section.
An outstanding feature for your alto saxophone soloist, this impressive composition is comprised of two contrasting and lyrical themes.
This solidly scored and dramatic march is characterized by colorful contrasting themes and powerful rhythms. Makes a great opener on any program!

Here's an excellent introduction to contrapuntal textures for young bands. The fugue form provides ample opportunities for all players to play the theme. An excellent learning experience as well as a dramatic performance piece!

Your young players will really "get-into" the rock flavor of this exciting yet easily learned piece. Even very inexperienced groups will soon be sounding their best and having a great time along the way!
LIGHTLY LATIN is a light "pop style" piece composed especially for younger bands. Interesting syncopated rhythms have been combined with lyrical melodic passages in a most engaging and effective way.

This exciting and dramatic composition skillfully presents the sophisticated sounds of the modern wind ensemble to your young band. With its strong themes and powerful rhythms, "BRAVADA" makes an exceptionally fine program addition.

An innovative musical journey through the sounds of the day. By combining the accompanying pre-recorded CD of popular video game sounds with your band, this powerful work will be a guaranteed hit with both your band and the audience!
Here's a lively excursion into the sounds and rhythms of bluegrass music. Cleverly conceived and skillfully written for younger bands, it's sure to be a big favorite.
Here's a brilliant and colorful trumpet feature that can be successfully performed spotlighting a soloist, duet or quartet.
This lyrical and colorful Latin selection has lots of melodic interest for all sections. Easy yet effective.
Spotlighting the percussion section, this dramatic piece is expertly scored for young bands.
This powerful and exciting march-like composition will open (or close) your program in spectacular style. Very popular and effective!

The 17th century hymn "Let All Mortal Flesh Keep Silence" forms the basis for this outstanding treatment. Inventive counterpoint, lush harmonies and an enticing modal flavor make it an excellent choice for either concert and contest.

Add a touch of high seas adventure to your next program with this rhapsodic treatment of familiar nautical themes. This piece celebrates the heritage of early sailors and their ships, the romance of going to sea and the songs they sang to make the long days and tedious work more tolerable. Featuring three famous Sea Chanties "Blow Ye Winds," "High Barnaby" and "Shenandoah" masterfully scored for intermediate level
Brilliantly scored for band, the contrasting styles of this composition make it a truly important and lasting addition to your band's library.

You can let out all the stops with this delightful selection that swings from start to finish. This march incorporates several different musical styles including cut-time "quick step" style, straight-ahead swing and dixieland. A Guaranteed audience favorite!

A beautiful carol presented in three verse settings. Although ideal for holiday programs, this enchanting arrangement is so good you'll want to use it one other programs as well. Exceptionally fine writing.

Written for the 500th anniversary of Columbus' voyage, this dramatic and heroic composition makes a perfect choice for contest of concert. A creative and memorable cross-curricular opportunity for your musicians and audience.
A musical saga of one of the world's greatest explorers, this heroic and exciting epic is loaded with power and drama making it ideal for concert or contest.
This fine march-styled composition contains some rather adventurous textures and harmonies yet has been skillfully written for the abilities of younger ensembles.
This interesting rock treatment of Beethoven's classic melody is certain to add variety and impact to your next performance!
Written to feature either solo trumpet or solo alto sax, this enchanting Latin-styled piece is sure to captivate your audience! Very effective.
Jay has adapted his powerful jazz ensemble chart for concert band and your players will love it! Use the track available below to accompaniy your band's live performance. Uniquely memorable!

This Elliot Del Borgo composition is a stately and melodic work that expertly explores the full range of sonoities and colors of the concert band. Contemporry harmonies and active rhythmic figurations give the piece an exciting flavor that builds to a dramatic conclustion. With interesting parts for all sections, this piece is equally rewarding for players and audience.
This solidly scored Spanish-flavored piece begins with a bravura main section which is contrasted by an enchanting mariachi section. EL CAMINO will have your band sounding its best in no time!
An outstanding contest-oriented piece that's exciting, dramatic and extremely impressive in performance! In addition, TEMPESTAS will be an exciting and rewarding piece to teach.
Add the excitement of Spain to your next concert with this dramatic selection! This strongly scored piece, influenced by the familiar pasa doble rhythm, will become a real favorite. Ole!
Here's a really brilliant band work! With its majestic British character and powerful sonorities, EXCALIBUR is destined to become a "classic" addition to your repertoire!
A dramatic interplay of dynamics, themes and colors characterizes this brilliant work which is especially suited for contest use.

An inventive composition which captures the fascinating sounds and colors of Far Eastern music amazingly well. The main melody is modal but the harmony, at times is more varied. "Asian Song" reflects some of the musical aspects of the many cultures that exist on that continent. Exceptionally appealing!

A descriptive overture by the composer of the critically acclaimed Joyant Music. "Cityscape" explores the vivid colors and textures of symphonic band while projecting some of the many moods that are experienced in the day of a great city.

A dramatic, programatic three movement suite which portrays an imaginative journey through the heavens.  Part 1: Universal Reception - powerful and assertive graphically depicting the awesome forces of intergalactic travel. Part 2: Moonwatch - peaceful, dream-like mood creating the effect of freely floating through space. Part 3: Skyscape - vividly portrays a panoramic view of the galaxy. An outstanding addition to

This dramatic overture is formally based upon the classic sonata-allegro form although the melodic and contrapuntal lines use contemporary resources and the harmony effectively uses fourth and fifth structures to exploit the tonal brilliance and unique sonorities of the concert band.

Noted composer of film and television, Jay Chattaway composed this powerful and gallant concert march which effectively recalls the glory and adventure of the tall sailing ships. Your band and audiences will love this impressive best-seller!
This brilliantly scored, dramatic composition is equally at home in concert or competition.

Songs of the American Revolution, a national hymn and two hundred years of American musical heritage are all blended together and combined with stylistic band sounds. Contained in this patriotic mosaic are "Yankee Doodle," "Chester" and "America, the Beautiful."

Written as a sincere invitation to celebrate the occasion of America's two-hundreth anniversary of independence. A powerful two movement work which impressively explores the varied resources of the modern concert band.

A set of variations on the familiar tune. The theme travels through various musical settings in the course of its "around-the-world" journey. ("British, German, Oriental and South-of-the-border.") An optional narrator part is included and can be quite effective, especially if performed using the different dialects.
The beautiful "Mary Had A Baby" and a rock-flavored "Go Tell It On The Mountain" are featured in this effective and highly playable arrangement.

Variations on a Theme by Grieg is designed to give your best players an opportunity to play a solo with band accompaniment. Using the famous Morning theme from the popular Peer Gynt Suite as the basis, a new composition is created that is a set of variations on this theme.
titre: Variations on a Theme by Greig

description: Fanfare Acclamations is a contest style piece that is bold and energetic. As the title implies is begins with a bold maestoso fanfare with punctuating percussion that leads to the active main theme in an up-tempo allegro.

Meet the Band is intended to be used as a recruitment piece at a recruitment concert. It introduces young students to all of the instruments and sections of the band. The narrator “Sam the Snare Drum” takes the students on a musical journey through the instrument of the band. Many of the instrumental themes will be familiar to the students from their use in the Yamaha Advantage Recorder Plus method. Each section and

Whispers is a lyrical composition that will be a perfect vehicle to teach musicianship, elegant phrasing, balance, blend and beauty of tone. Beautiful melodies are given numerous orchestrational and harmonic treatments to create a musical journey that will be pleasing to performers and audiences alike.

Lullaby for Christmas is a unique combining of popular lullabies such as the Brahm’ Lullaby and Hush-a-bye Baby with the favorite Christmas carols Away In a Manger and O, Holy Night. A beautiful and subtle arrangement to celebrate the Christmas season!

Fluer-de-lis March is written to introduce the march form and style to young musicians. Playing marches is part of the heritage of the band and is an importance style that the students should learn to play. The form of this composition includes the traditional modulation to the subdominant at the Trio.

Recorder Rag was composed to feature members of your elementary recorder class playing along with the band for recruitment purposes. The ragtime style was chosen for its fun appeal to both player and audience alike. Place the recorder section at the front of the band so they can be heard and seen by their parents. This will be a smash hit and a great recruitment tool.

The Fifers is designed to give your best players an opportunity to play a solo with band accompaniment. Originally composed for harpsichord by Jean-Francois Dandrieu, this lively piece is written in a Baroque style and is perfect for reinforcing sixteenth note rhythms.

Impressions is a heartfelt composition in a lyrical style. Beautiful melodies are given numerous orchestrational and harmonic treatments to create a musical journey that will be pleasing to performers and audiences.

Talons of Fire is an aggressive, energetic contest style composition that everyone will enjoy performing. It contains bold fanfares, strong percussion interjections and angular rhythms that will be thrilling for students and audience alike.

The Bells of Christmas, a medley of popular Christmas carols, incorporates the sounds of ringing bells and chimes as a unifying theme. The piece presents O Tanenbaum, Deck the Halls, Joy to the World and other snippets of holiday favorites in a variety of styles from fanfare gestures to beautiful chorale type settings.
Festival Chorale and March is design to reinforce newly learned eighth note rhythms and to give students a contest/festival style piece that will improve their musicianship.
Jupiter the famous Gustav Holst composition is arranged for flute or clarinet or alto saxophone soloist with band accompaniment or it can be played by band alone.
Flourish is a great concert opener or closer. This fanfare style piece is perfect for contests and festivals and excellent for teaching form.

Winter Holidays is unique in that it combines four favorite holiday songs of both Christmas and Hanukah. The songs are heard alone and together, at one point combining three of the melodies in a musical celebration exemplifying both the uniqueness and the unifying forces of the holiday season.
Geology: The Study of Rock combines a rock bass line, percussion groove and a melody with a little twist into a fun to play crowd-pleasing composition.
Primus has the most limited range and technical demands of any piece in the series. It only uses 5 notes Concert Bb to F and is a great first performance piece.

If you are looking for a piece that can be used to combine your Elementary, Middle School and High School bands for a mass performance - here it is! Band-o-rama march contains parts for elementary, middle school/intermediate, and high school/advancing players. The parts marked A are for the high school level, B parts for middle school and C parts for elementary. If a part does not have an indication of A, B or C, it

Prestige is designed to introduce March style and form to the young band. Although it only contains the first 7 notes found in most band methods, Concert A to G, it provides a meaningful march experience.
Reflections combines chorale-style playing with contemporary harmonies. It is a perfect piece to reinforce the teaching of phrasing and overall musical performance.
A Natural Blues is composed in a traditional 12 bar blues form. The use of the A natural is a perfect way to reinforce this note when it is taught.

titre: Well Met, My Own True Love

description: A delightful set of variations on “What Shall We Do With a Drunken Sailor?” All players get the tune in variations that range from rowdy to whimsical to introspective. A clever setting of an old favorite! Lots of fun!

Stunningly gorgeous! There are many setting of this eighteenth century Irish tune “O Waly, Waly,” and this is one of the most beautiful. The optional vocal part gives it an extra special touch. Breathtaking!

After an opening gong, the composition’s motif is presented by solo flute, accompanied by soft low woodwinds, then clarinets, then tutti. The main theme, a somber melody in Dorian mode, is first introduced in a slow tempo, then as an agitated Allegro with aggressive percussion. Excellent for contest or festival.
An inspired free setting of the revival spiritual  "Zion’s Walls." Beautiful melodic material is developed throughout. Lots of color and grandeur all packed into one great piece! A masterpiece!

This piece is a real treat! Pierre has created a frolicking portrayal of a morning walk. "An early morning walk is a blessing for the whole day," wrote Thoreau, and this tune will leave everyone in a sunny mood. Skillfully composed and simply delightful!
titre: A Walk In The Morning Sun

description: Feature one or all of your trombones in this blockbuster! Three of Wagner’s most famous melodies “Pilgrim’s Chorus,” “Ride of the Valkyries,” and the “Lohengrin” Prelude are featured in this magnificent showstopper! Unforgettable!
Bold and aggressive, This is the first movement of a four-movement work titled "Olympus: Four Mythological Legends." Each movement published separately.

This masterwork is a combination of paddling songs, love songs and songs of celebration describing the hearty French Canadian fur traders of Canada and the upper Midwest in the eighteenth and early nineteenth centuries. A sure winner! Three movements: I. En Roulant  II. A La Claire Fontaine III. "Rendezvous"

Inspired by the debka, a Middle Eastern folk dance, this exuberant piece gives less experienced bands the opportunity to sound big and mature. Supported by lively percussion, this piece “cooks!” Everyone will love it!

Get ready for the applause! A great piece for concerts, festivals and honor bands. Featuring Tchaikovsky’s most famous melodies: “Sleeping Beauty,” “The Nutcracker,” “Swan Lake,” and “Symphony ‘Pathetique,’” topped off with the “1812 Overture!” A favorite of players and audiences!

A musical depiction of the largest Tyrannosaurus Rex skeleton in existence. Mysterious, dramatic music describes the huge animal that lived 67 million years ago: its development from a hatchling to a vicious predator, its episodic life and demise. A super exciting programmatic masterwork!

Tchaikovsky’s beloved march comes bounding up from the pages of this excellent transcription. Sweeping woodwinds and powerful brass and, on, those beautiful Tchaikovsky melodies! A real adventure for players and audience. Fantastic!

It’s all here; the heroic “Big Tunes” with radiant trumpets, sonorous horns, the threatening rhythmic motif from the trombones and the incessant foreboding ostinato. Give your band and your audience the experience of this classic masterwork.

The terror and tragedy of the Russian Revolution’s "Bloody Sunday" is brutally depicted in this music. Your players and audience will be caught up in the drama of this outstanding arrangement. Very intense!

An exquisite setting of Percy Grainger’s beloved lyrical Christmas gift to the world! Skillfully and painstakingly arranged to keep all of the tempo, dynamic and expressive markings of Grainger’s original. A glowing tribute within a breathtakingly beautiful setting!

The “animation” comes from the vigorous percussion; the brasses and woodwinds provide the “suspense.” (Hundreds of suspensions – explicit and hidden.) Lots of variety in articulation, volume and tone color. A unique and wonderful piece that is out-of-the ordinary for bands of this level.
Very appealing work and a wonderful vehicle for acquainting students with the slow Blues-Jazz style. From Broege’s “Marietta Suite.” A lot of fun for players and audience!

gets two “A’s” for “Audience Appeal” and two B’s “ for “Bones” (t-bones and funny-bones). Perform it at 120 as a march or 144 as a gallop. At any tempo, this 1908 gem is a sure winner for your concert! So FUN!

From the brilliant opening fanfare to the big closing crescendo, this piece is a vibrant dialogue of “call and response” from every section of the band. The spirited two-measure theme appears throughout, sometimes surrounded by staccato punctuation, sometimes accompanied by flowing sostenuto lines. Superb writing for young band!
This is beautiful band music of the highest order! Inspired by the composer’s mother’s stories of her childhood in Ireland. Simply beautiful!
titre: The Silent Hills Of My Childhood

description: A Dramatic opening fanfare, a lively main theme, and a lovely slow melody superimposed over "Shenandoah." Lots of excitement and contrast for the developing band. A great showpiece!
Unbelievable brightness in the great scoring of this delightful country dance which showcases the band’s many colors. A work of unbridled Renaissance joyfulness!

What a great way to start a concert or festival! This popular Latin motto is musically illuminated in this adventurous composition inspiring all to make the most of every moment with energy, passion and optimism! Valiant, bold and beautiful!

A lot of wonderful contrasts in this gem of a young band piece: minor-major tonality, canonic-fugal entrances, accented syncopation and a percussion feature. Full of interest and a perfect way to inspire confidence in young musicians!

A beautiful blending of “Dona Nobis Pacem” and “Silent Night,” inspired by a December 1914 incident, when World War I British and German troops held a Christmas Eve truce, singing carols and exchanging food and gifts. A lovely addition to any seasonal concert.

Another wonderful folksong setting scored especially for the young band. Beautiful lines and harmonies grace this gem. Accessible to young players, this gorgeous piece is worthy of performance by all ensembles!
A magnificent work evoking the days of knights and castles. A relentless sense of spirit. Written for all those with goals and dreams. Grand and inspiring!
This straight-ahead march just sparkles! Bright, positive melodies and broad, noble melodies, punctuated by a rugged “dog-fight” – this brilliant march has everything!

An absolutely gorgeous chorale weaves its way into a delightful little country wedding dance tune. After a restatement of the chorale, the presto sequences of the dance tune makes a spirited finale. Beautiful writing!

Two Midwestern folk tunes, one tragic and one humorous, skillfully combined. The first section, “The Pinery Boy,” conveys a feeling of grandeur and beauty of the land. The second section quotes “The Turkey Song.” Common melodic patterns between the two songs make them sound as though they are related. A wonderful masterwork!
Dramatic and Bold, this is the final movement of a four-movement work titled "Olympus: Four Mythological Legends."  Each movement is published separately.
Three well-known American folksongs, "Down in the Valley," "Skip to My Lou," and "Cindy," are featured in this thoughtful and delightful arrangement for young concert band.

What could be more fun than a march from the Roaring Twenties originally written for banjo! Treat your players and audience to band music of a bygone era. Imagine being under the Big-Top with music to accompany acrobats, wild animals and clowns! Great fun!

This jaunty little Scottish tune travels through several artful variations and then is joined with Auld Lang Syne. Get your audience involved with the optional vocal part to make it an extra grand finale. Fine for concert and festival, or for a dedication or farewell ceremony. Cheerful and touching!
titre: O Whistle and I'll Come To Ye

description: A bright tune in F Major contrasts nicely with folk-like melodies in Aeolian and Dorian modes to describe a long-ago England. Very attractive and worthy music for young bands!

Powerful melodies and fleeting rhythms propel this dynamic piece from beginning to end. Band members are invited to create their own musical journey as they play this exciting work. Very imaginative, creative and inspirational!

A glowing musical tribute to President John F. Kennedy and his hopeful vision for the future. Inspired by the “We stand today on the edge of a new frontier” speech and beautifully orchestrated. A bold, noble and exciting piece!

"Mythos" is the Greek word for ‘story’ or ‘legend.’ All the elements of Greek mythology are captured in this exciting piece: the hero, the peril, the adventure and the conquest. This overture in D minor contains appealing melodies, plenty of contrasts and great percussion! Very adventuresome!
The conductor’s score outlines a great way to teach the band about Rondo Form. Lots of excitement and color along with imaginative percussion scoring makes this a piece musician’s love!

"Music from the Great Hall" is a set of two Renaissance dance forms. The first movement, "A Toye," is light and delightful. The second movement, "The King's Morisco," is a contrast of bombastic mysterious openeing sounds before settling into the traditional dance feel. Transport your audience into the Great Hall of the castle with these stylistic works.

Relentless rhythmic drive! Memorable melodic lines! Unstoppable syncopation! From the first ticks, clicks, and clangs of the hi-hat, snare drum and brake drum, this piece moves! Bold melodies and pointillist flashes toward a powerful finale makes this music that young people love to play!

Early railroad songs, gold-rush tunes and African-American spirituals molded into an exuberant, spirited musical celebration! A masterpiece! Sure to become an important part of the concert band repertoire! Movements: I. Patrick on the Railway. II. Sweet Betsy, III. Little David, Play On!

The Native American motif is recognizable from the very first six notes of the melody. Exemplary music for young band where just about everyone gets to play the theme. Don’t be surprised to hear the musicians humming the six-note melody on their way out of rehearsal! Catchy!
A delightful transcription for band or wind ensemble based upon the second movement of Haydn’s Symphony No. 63. Classic!

A jaunty 6/8 hunting horn fanfare launches this piece into a whirlwind of Italian fun. Based on happy melodies from Rossini’s story of Cinderella. Filled with rhythmic verve, rapid-fire motion and the famed Rossini crescendo! Awesome!
A bright little French children’s song goes through seven delightful variations and ends with a rousing can-can! Beautifully written!

This fiery dance was the high point of Glinka’s opera “A Life for the Czar.” A great way to bring The Russian Nationalistic Movement in music to your curriculum. A non-stop band showpiece! Impressive!

This work begins with great energy and intensity, and builds vigorously throughout. A science-fiction adventure movie theme is depicted, allowing childhood imaginations to supply the details. Outstanding writing, especially for the percussion, who are featured from beginning to end. A powerhouse for young band!
A little march that’s big on nobility, brilliance and pride. The strong rhythms and a bright melody will engage everyone and bring a spark to your next concert or festival.

Some of Tchaikovsky’s most inspired and beautiful music. Joan of Arc’s forest prayer and a noble march from the coronation scene are combined in a great concert band arrangement. Ideal for concert and festival performances.
titre: Joan Of Arc Hymn and March

description: Bittersweet, gossamer sonorities for winds. Sure to evoke nostalgia and memories of youthful "hometown" days. Inspired by a poem. Gorgeous writing!
A beautiful musical portrait. Optional narriation text excerpted from "Requiem" by Robert Louis Stevenson. Very moving.

A big, brawny piece imaging places in Texas. This work contains four big tunes that require lots of good players (including a pianist) and lots of percussion (including a starter’s pistol)! There’s nothing else quite like this bold piece! Movements: I. Coyote Call (2:10) II. Vinegarroons (1:14) III. The Grand Courthouse Clock (3:11) IV. The Greater Milam County Armadillo Race (3:30)
Majestic fanfares, noble themes, powerful counterpoint and exciting percussion! A Sparkling, brilliant masterpiece for band!
A medley of Highland Dance, "The Lass of Gowrie," "Bythe and Merry Was She," "Scotland the Brave" and "Auld Lang Syne." Great fare for the young band.
Bold heroic music! Plenty of drama and contrast. Exciting percussion. Sure to capture the imagination of performers and audience alike!

The piece starts with an air of mystery, a bit of darkness and curious light before powerful sounds echo through the ensemble. Heartbeats can be heard throughout the piece. Strong melodies, tense harmonies and aggressive percussion! Dramatic and imaginative!
A great way to introduce young bands to 6/8 time. Delightful!

Lots of energy in this piece from the very beginning where players are invited to stomp their feet. Plenty of excitement and contrast as a boisterous little melody is tossed around the band, accompanied by a variety of colorful points of light, and highly active percussion. Based on an ancient Japanese song, “Moko Yokocho.” A treat for the young band and their audience!
This beautiful composition is based on an old Irish folk tune used by Thomas Moore for his poem in 1815.
titre: Has Sorrow Thy Young Days Shaded

description: Beginning with a jaunty snare drum cadence, followed by a happy-go-lucky melody that says, “I’m glad I’m alive, and I want to march!” This is one of Knoener’s earliest and most popular marches. A favorite, forever!

This gorgeous work chronicles the emotional connection between humans and other complex life; all of us threads in a great tapestry. The composer creates a colorful palette with lyrical melodies and many moving inner voices. An inspired work for concert band.

From the brilliant opening fanfare to the noble march, this little masterwork sounds more like an adventure movie score than a young band piece. This is a creative and spirited work for introducing students to 6/8 meter. Sounding a lot harder than it really is, this is a very likeable piece for opening a concert, or music festival.

Here is a terrific choice for your holiday concert! A joyful medley of Spanish carols: “Fun, Fum, Fum,” “As Cold December flies,” “Tonight a Babe is Born,” “Riu, Riu, Chu,” and “Companions, All Sing Loudly.” A brilliant score! Feliz Navidad!

This wonderful arrangement of three Renaissance tunes, "A Toye," "Tell mee Daphne," and "The New Sa-hoo," will add color to your bands repretoire. Lots of percussion and interweaving parts makes this a delight to rehearse and perform!
Noble music that really touches the heart. A wonderful epic piece to play for important ceremonies and special events.
An action-packed adventure for the young band with a nod to the Sturm und Drang overtures of yesteryear. Excitement for every player!
Beautiful and sensitive writing showcases your ensemble’s lyrical side with this well-known and beloved American mountain ballad. Brilliant!

A great young band concert opener with a noble fanfare and majestic theme. The theme is beautifully developed and accompanied by colorful “points of light” from the upper woodwinds. Dedicated to the space shuttle Discovery. Exemplary young band literature.

All the sweep and grandeur of Wagner’s music encapsulated in a symphonic miniature for young band. Two of his noblest themes are joined in a concert piece that will inspire, yet not fatigue, young players. High quality educational music!
An underlying driving rhythm propels this lively piece through various dramatic episodes. An electrifying opus that is really exciting and impressive sounding!
Driving rhythmic melodies surround a gorgeous chorale in this imaginative work. Lots of color, lots of excitement and extraordinary percussion! Very unique and a true winner!

This festive sounding march is reminiscent of those performed in Europe. European bands utilize euphoniums in harmony, and this is the case with "Come to the Festival Tent." Very powerful and articulate!
A charming little overture, complete with hurdy-gurdy effect. Based on two American folksongs: "The Animal Fair" and "Johnny’s So Long at the Fair." A favorite of bands and audiences.

One of the most famous marches written by VanderCook while he was Bandmaster of the LaPearl Circus in the 1890s. Skillfully arranged for modern bands, there is lots of fun and excitement in this old-timer! Wonderful!

Oh, what fun it is to find a forgotten Christmas piece by Gustav Holst! Christmas Day is a set of variations on “In Dulci Jubilo” (“Good Christian Men, Rejoice”) with interwoven portions of “God Rest Ye Merry, Gentlemen,” “The First Nowell,” and “Come Ye Lofty, Come Ye Lowly.” A charming piece for your holiday concert!
This third movement from "Triptych" begins with a solemn chorale, then dives into alternating fanfares and lyricism, finally leading to a rousing finale. Thrilling!
Bring the flavor of 19th century music to your next concert with this tender piece, originally scored for four-part chorus and organ. Expertly arranged and an excellent change of pace!

This beautiful Chorale is Number 176 of Bach’s 371 Harmonized Chorales, Erstanden ist der Heil’ge Christ; the Fugue is number 4 of his Eight Little Preludes and Fugues.  Literature of the highest quality for concert or festival performance.
Spice up your next concert with this snappy rag. A 1910 classic skillfully arranged for today’s ensembles! What a find!

"The Coventry Carol" is treated slowly in chorale style in opening, followed by a jig-like scherzo setting of "We Three Kings." The carols/styles alternate throughout the work with the melody of "The Coventry Carol" eventually appearing in the style of "We Three Kings." A intriguing treatment of two traditional carols that adds variety to your holiday concert.

A masterpiece for younger bands. The lonely, mysterious “chant,” accompanied by fragments of muted percussion goes through several harmonic transformations before giving way to a big, bold celebratory refrain. Great melodies for everyone!

Noble in spirit with a nice mix of tonalities and harmonies for beginning bands. The great melodies and countermelodies for give everyone the opportunity make music. A wonderful first concert selection.

A whimsical, captivating composition with a nostalgic nod to the circus, the polka, and ragtime. Lots of little parodies, jokes and caricatures are paraded out before us in this delightful escapade. Great fun for everyone!

Three contrasting movements based on folk tunes: "Britons, Raise our Banners High," "Men of Harlech," "Barbara Allen," "Adieu, Dundee," and "Auld Lang Syne." Appealing music with lots of variety. Movements: I. Marching Song  II. Barbara Allen  III. Farewell, Dundee

This setting opens with a hearty cadence of snare drums and field drums, followed by the addition of fifes (piccolo and flute). The A section features ‘Bonnie Eloise,’ a favorite tune of both armies during the Civil War. The B section is original material. The love of Civil War music is evident in this fine arrangement. Very uplifting!
sous_titre: The Belle Of The Mohawk Vale

description: A wonderful way to introduce less experienced ensembles to Ragtime! Fun from top to bottom!
A simply gorgeous, melt-your-heart piece. Beautiful and pensive.

What a way to open your young band’s first concert! This little march has everything! A straight-ahead first strain, a nice little flute-clarinet feature in the second strain, a noble “big tune” trio, and there is even a “dog-fight” break-strain! A real winner!
A little march with everything! Catchy first strain, marcato second strain, noble Trio and blustery “dog-fight.” Performers and audiences of all ages will love this march!

This very appealing piece describes an early twentieth century Fourth of July. The band is heard faintly in the distance, coming closer; the band is right next to you; the band is passing, then fading away. A very attractive "patrol" march for young bands. A winner!

Brilliant antiphonal fanfares announce this musical picture of an old Scottish castle by the North Sea—followed by many ‘dialogues’ between very unique choirs of winds and percussion. An extraordinary masterwork for the young, advancing band.

Anton Bruckner (1824-1896) is known today primarily for his massive symphonies for orchestra. However, he also composed a number of vocal works for forces of varying size and character, including three settings of the "Ave Maria." This setting was originally for alto voice and organ, and ulike the other settings, dates from Bruckner's mature years. It reflects all of the notable characteristics of his style - simple

This glorious piece just glows with hope and positivity! After a brief introduction by chimes and timpani, trumpets and trombones announce the rambunctious theme, and Accolade is off and running, fast and furious, until the very end! An excellent opener or closer, or for an occasion when you’d like to honor someone. Accolades and applause!

This charming, gentle piece depicts images from children's imaginations and blends them with an elegant jazz waltz to create a special quiet musical escape. It is easy to envision looking up at the summer clouds with this captivating depiction. Lovely and engaging!

A magnificent tour-de-force for solo trumpet and wind ensemble! Composed by Jay Chattaway for trumpet virtuoso Jens Lindemann, "Shenandoah Fantasy" brilliantly showcases the full range of trumpet virtuosity. Contrasting sections feature lyrical playing, rapid tonguing, jazz inflections, and brilliant range and dexterity. An astonishing addition to solo trumpet repertoire! Set includes oversized spiral-bound score.

titre: Variations on a Theme by Tschaikowsky

description: This piece is written to showcase your beginners using only the first six notes. Each instrument has an important role to play in this piece. Use it on one of your first concerts with beginners.

On the Shore of Baffin Bay is an exciting new composition for today’s mature bands. Written with a exciting rhythms, percussion and a melody that will be remembered, this work is guaranteed to be a winner. Highly recommended.
titre: On The Shore of Baffin Bay

description: Beginning with a beautiful chorale and developing into an exciting dance-like setting, Slavonic Chorale and Dance is a perfect work for today’s bands. Your students will enjoy rehearsing this work. An excellent selection for any occasion.

Dark Eyes is a Russian Folk Song. This arrangement featuring Solo Clarinet with Concert Band includes a short cadenza and a slow highly embellished melodic section which is followed by a jazzy conclusion. A real audience pleaser which is fun to perform.

A lush treatment for younger bands of Poor Wayfarin’ Stranger and Shenandoah. Balanced treatment of the melody and accompaniment involves all of the band’s sonorities and gives ample room for teaching musicality and phrasing. Highly recommended!
Jazzy fun for first year players! Easy swing style and attention to articulation makes this piece fun for kids and a delight for your audience!
Kings Street March is a delightful march full of rhythmic vitality and rich harmonic textures. Written in a compact style, this march can be a great addition to any concert program.

This award-winning composition is based on the Delta Omicron Keynote, a charming piece from the professional music fraternity's songbook. A tightly-constructed work, virtually every melodic idea is derived from a portion of the Keynote theme which binds the piece together. By turns majestic, energetic, poignant, and triumphant, this piece has it all!

The influence of Claude T. Smith is heavily present in this piece, a perfect addition to any festival or concert program. Safely scored for most any band, this work is easily accessible for both performers and audiences. The themes from the fast and slow sections ingeniously combine for a thrilling finale!

Composed for woodwind artist Gary Foster, the “Suite for Solo Flute, Clarinet and Alto Sax” is a perfect concert showpiece for the multiple woodwind instrumentalist. The opening allegro features flute, demonstrating both technical prowess as well as a jazz-influenced lyrical theme. A return to the allegro is followed by a cadenza, then a switch to clarinet for a haunting and beautiful Lento, and a showy waltz.
titre: Suite For Solo Flute, Clarinet and Alto Saxophone

description: Introduce your younger ensembles to Spanish march style with this wonderful composition full of colorful percussion scoring. An excellent vehicle for emphasizing clean articulations and dramatic dynamic contrasts. An exciting work for contest and festivals. Positively captivating!
A wonderful first march by the young Claude T. Smith. This work is especially challenging for the trumpet section. Full of power, this march will stir the spirits of performers and audiences alike.

The horns set the mood right from the start in this exciting work for advanced middle school ensembles. With syncopated accompaniment, well thought out transitions and occasional 7/8 bars, this stunning overture is also suitable for high school concert and festival use.
Beautiful scoring of a traditional folk song with a contemporary feel. Well suited for younger ensembles being introduced to lyrical performance material.

The lovely choral beginning features the familiar carol "Good Christian Men, Rejoice," and sets the groundwork for this unique work. The piece features soli opportunity for bassoon and trombone, followed by a flute, clarinet and horn trio. Modulations, tempo changes, and meter changes add a unique flair. Temple blocks are a must. Programmable for any time of the year, but especially joyful for the holiday season.
titre: Symphonic Variations On In Dulci Jubilo

description: A bold exciting march expertly blended with the English tune “Terra Beata” more commonly known as the hymn “This Is My Father’s World.” An exciting arrangement for advancing ensembles.
titre: Symphonic March On An English Hymn Tune

description: This delightful multi-meter overture is a treasure! The light detached rhythmic style and lively tempo drive the music. A flute, saxophone and trumpet solo in the middle section give it added variety. Challenging and rewarding.

Take your performers and audience on a trip to a South American festival! Skillful scoring with extensive doubling and cues allow performance success for smaller ensembles. The Latin melody and lively rhythms make this an engaging work. For maximum effect, a full percussion section with mallet instrumentation is needed. A great change of pace for your next performance.

Beautifully written to ensure success with younger ensembles. This overture is wonderfully developed with captivating rhythmic themes and dynamics. The reoccurring theme allows players the opportunity to recognize their role within the ensemble. A solid work for concert and festival performances.

Tucked between the sparkling Allegro theme is a lovely contrasting lyrical section. Wonderful for getting young players excited about lyrical pieces. The flute section especially will enjoy their role with the trumpets having an opportunity to shine as well. A young band favorite!

A dramatic introduction opens this work which is based on two contrasting movements. After a lush melodic section, a vigorous and playful chase (caccia) follows, painting a colorful picture in sound, leading to an exciting conclusion. Your performers and audience will be delighted with the playfulness portrayed.
Serene and lovely describes this chorale prelude. Highlighted by long tones, dynamic contrasts and flowing melodic lines, this work is an effective chorale, or beautiful asset to any concert.
This work is a dynamic and inventive piece set in a traditional military march style.
A perfect concert march for contest or festival programming without high technical demands. Fashioned after the European-style march, this is an exceptional choice for less experienced bands.
This light-hearted galop features the percussion section. Delightful!

This jubilant composition is very challenging and powerful. Two principal themes are presented which develop through the use of varying accompaniments, ensemble timbres, rhythmic techniques and solo passages. A wonderful showcase for concert or festival use.
Attention grabbing right from the start! This powerful work unfolds into a rich, beautiful hymn setting which is followed by a driving rhythmic theme. Full of power and inspiration.

This impressive overture begins triumphantly and offers opportunities for trumpets, horns, percussion, clarinets, trombones and saxophones to be featured. A perfect selection to show off your band's skills in a concert or festival setting.

South American rhythms and melodies were the inspiration for this exciting work. An abundance of syncopation, meter changes and modulations will keep performers and audiences engaged. Effective and appealing programing!

Intricate rhythmic patterns are developed and unique harmonic texture is created through imaginative symphonic band scoring in this exciting and spectacular piece. Intriguing for performer and audiences alike.
Challenging, yet gratifying, this work takes the introductory statement through a variety of treatments. Each section plays a key role which culminates the true spirit of this work.

Commissioned by the National Honorary Band Fraternity, Kappa Kappa Psi and the National Honorary Band Sorority of Tau Beta Sigma, this sparkling masterwork contains four distinctive movements highlighting Smith’s use of unique harmonic language, lavish melodies and imaginative rhythms. A virtuosic work for advanced wind ensembles.

Lyrical woodwind solos open this masterwork followed by brass solos and Inventive variations on a popular folk hymn. Smith has created an exceptional piece for advanced wind ensembles perfect for concerts or festivals.

A bold fanfare opens this work. The music continues with a wonderful engaging melody. Feature your solo clarinet player in a beautifully written solo accompanied by poignant counterpoint. The piece wraps up with the same incredible energy as the beginning, bringing the whole musical experience full circle before the rousing finish.

This work captures the full range of timbres that a band can create in this superb hymn adaptation. The transparency in the simple settings, combined with a tasteful arranging of a hymn tune, followed by melodic counter melodies set this piece apart from others.
titre: Were You There When They Crucified My Lord

description: A masterfully scored work of this timeless Christmas hymn. The different settings of the melody engage the performer and the listener from the solemn beginning, through the bright middle, and powerful ending. An excellent addition to your library.
This rousing traditional march will keep the toes tapping and the musicians smiling. Everyone has the opportunity to play the melody! A wonderful choice for a concert opener.

Bands will enjoy performing this Theme-and-Variations based on the English folk song "Forest Green," which served as the music for several different popular hymns. Several opportunities for solos, this work is perfect for concert or festival. Enjoyable!
titre: Variations on an English Folk Song

description: Using the melody for 'Auld Lang Syne', this march is performed in three very distinct styles. Designed for younger bands, it will sound fantastic with your groups.

This two-part piece for younger bands opens with long and lush melodies in the Invocation followed by an energetic Jubiloso section with driving ostinatos and soaring melodies found throughout the band.

Written for accomplished soloist Brian Bowman, principal Euphonium in the US Air Force Band, as a commissioned work under conductor Col. Arnald Gabriel, this composition is for virtuoso soloist and concert band. It calls for expressive phrasing especially through the Lento and Andante sections. Smith incorporates mixed meters and his signature 7/8 bar to create a dance-like lift. A concert showpiece that contains a
sous_titre: for Solo Euphonium and Symphonic Band

description: Bold brass statements make this an impressive sounding number (incl. 4 scores)
A light Latin tune which features the young percussion section. Feel free to add other latin percussion instruments if you have a large percussion section! FUN!
"The Knights of Pythias"

titre: In The Glory Of The Moonlight
How Are You Goin' To Wet Your Whistle?

description: Composed for the U. S. Naval Academy at Annapolis, Maryland (1921).
One of the most rousing marches ever composed, "Semper Fidelis" (Always Faithful) is the official march of the United States Marine Corps. Composed 1888.

This rollicking 6/8 march was one of several gems penned by Lt. Cmdr. Sousa as part of his patriotic efforts during WWII. Composed for the essential Liberty Loan campaigns of wartime, this is a lesser known Sousa gem. Stirring!
One of Sousa’s most universally recognized marches, this 1894 gem is a perennial audience favorite!
Composed for the Cotton States Exposition of 1895, at which Sousa’s Band was a featured attraction.
(1890) Composed for the Washington, DC Central High School drill team, this has remained one of Sousa's most beloved marches.
Composed in 1899, one of Sousa's most brilliant and energetic marches!
Composed for the Paris Exposition of 1900, and premiered by the Sousa Band on its first trip to Europe. Awe inspiring!
titre: Hail To The Spirit Of Liberty

description: "Knock a Man Down" "Away for Rio" "Haul the Bowline" "The Ballade of Billy Taylor" "It's Time for Us to Leave Her" "Put Up Clearing Gear" "Hoodah Day" "A-Roving"
Contains "Silent Night, Holy Night" and "Best Be The Tie That Binds"
Medley One-Step
One of the great "old line" marches from both worlds of circus bands and concert bands. A "barn-burner" from start to finish!
